      "type": "html",
      "text": "<i>[[Unit Test]]s are not a \"heavy artifact.\" This is a misuse of 'heavy' and 'artifact' as used by [[Extreme Programming]]. \"Heavy\" methodologies are weighed down by the requirement to produce \"artifacts\" - an artifact is a document that describes the software but isn't part of writing code, and so must be maintained as a separate task. In [[Test First Programming]], [[Unit Test]]s contribute directly to writing the code (the test code and production code have a symbiotic relationship - each checks the other, like the hands in the Escher drawing that draw each other). So they are not \"heavy artifacts\"! -- [[Apoorva Muralidhara]]</i>",
